I make this dish often. It is quick, easy, and just delicious. I usually use whole wheat pasta. I add white wine after the onions/garlic and reduce a bit, and sometimes throw in a dash of crushed red pepper. The raisins make the dish (regular raisins work fine too if you don't have golden raisins handy) as do good quality tuna, flavorful extra virgin olive oil, and fresh parsley.

