Rating: 3
Quite tasty, and very easy to make. I made this on the fly so I substituted broiled bluefish I had made over the weekend using another delicious epi recipe : http://www.epicurious.com/recipes/food/views/Broiled-Bluefish-Fillets-with-Fennel-Mayonnaise-14237 I also added some sun-dried tomatoes, and like a previous reviewer subbed in 1/2 a cup of white wine for some of the pasta water. While most of the changes I made were due to availability of ingredients and/or personal taste, I do recommend one change to the recipe. I suggest you do not add the parsley until the end, when you mix the pasta and the sauce together -- off heat.

