Rating: 3
What a surprise! I was desperate to make something for dinner/lunches, I had minimal food in the house and wasn't feeling very motivated to go out to the store or spend money. So I was browsing the recipes section for something with canned tuna and was actually suprised I found any recipes at all. I took a look at this recipe and I happened to have all the ingredients on hand so I thought I would give it a try. Despite being a little concerned about the combination of flavours, I was impressed with the end result. I used organic whole wheat rotini instead of linguini as that was what I had on hand, but I think that only added more depth to the flavour. And I used a fresh onion (not sure what the deal was with the frozen onions...aside from convenience, but seriously how long does it take to chop an onion?). I couldn't believe how well these flavours blended. I loved the bursts of sweet raisins in one bite and salty capers in the next, all in a "creamy" tuna "sauce". I probably won't make this one on a regular basis, but I'll definitely keep this in my collection for something different once in a while.

